<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-07T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1753</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-07T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                            1918, 3 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received May 7, 2.50
                                    p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your May 1, 5 p.m. My telegrams April 25, 5 p.m.,<note n="2" xml:id="d202fn2"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_137">p. 137</ref>.</note> April 27, 1 p.m.,<note n="3" xml:id="d202fn3"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_140">p. 140</ref>.</note> April 30, 2 p.m.,<note n="4" xml:id="d202fn4"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_147">p. 147</ref>.</note> give the information
                                available. The movement, <pb facs="0245" n="155" xml:id="pg_155"/>
                                avowedly administrative, is believed to be primarily political and
                                to aim at constituting a government for Siberia with the same
                                personnel after military success achieved with assistance from
                                Allies or Japanese alone.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_RPS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>